    "summary": "Planful publishes public REST API documentation for structured planning and data-load workflows, including data load rule retrieval, data transfer, file transfer, and callback-enabled execution tracking.",
    "description": "Manufactured OpenAPI artifact for Planful REST APIs. This file was synthesized by Last Mile from curated research JSON and is not vendor-certified. Use it as an agent-consumable starting point, then validate paths, schemas, authentication, and server URLs with the vendor before production use. Planful's public API site documents REST APIs for structured planning, dynamic planning, platform integrations, and data-load workflows. The public Data Load API examples show authenticated retrieval of data load rules and list rule types such as Data, Segment Hierarchies, Entity Hierarchies, Workforce Planning, External Source Model, and Writeback DLR. The public examples and collection references also describe transfer flows, file-based transfer, execution tracking, and callback-based processing for loading data into Planful models. This is a write-capable planning integration surface, but it does not represent asset or telemetry data. Asset data is Unsupported. Telemetry data is Unsupported. Writeback is Supported.",
